My mom... I was in Ottawa over the weekend (July 13-14) to celebrate my grandmother's 95th birthday. She's been riding public transit in Ottawa for 70 years so to celebrate the city gave us a bus driven by my grandma's favourite driver for the day. The bus ticker read "Rosie's Birthday Bus". There was about 20 of us on an hour long tour of the city. Granny Rose absolutely loved it...
My nieces Annika (left) and Rebecca (right) on the bus... Best large.

fields.title: Duct tape
fields.description: Between Harbord and College street. There's a Tim Horton's cup in the green recycling box in the foreground (Tim Horton's, or Timmy's as it is affectionately called, is a Canadian coffee & donut chain. It has a cult following here in Toronto and all over Canada). Every year Timmy's employs an aggressive ad campaign called Roll up the Rim to Win: you can win nothing, or coffee or cars. People go nuts for it.
